---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Get started" description="Orient yourself before reaching for Groundwork components">
  <section class="gw-section">
    <div class="gw-width gw-stack--lg">
      <div class="gw-prose">
        <h1 class="gw-heading-l">Get started</h1>
        <p>Groundwork is a small, opinionated design system. Before you reach for a component, understand the constraints it works inside: a closed token set, a two-tier token architecture, and restrictive React APIs that make accessible composition the obvious path.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="gw-grid">
        <article class="gw-card gw-stack--sm">
          <h2 class="gw-heading-s"><a class="gw-link" href="/get-started/why-groundwork/">Why Groundwork</a></h2>
          <p class="gw-body--sm">The problem Groundwork solves, the bets it makes, and what it deliberately leaves out.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="gw-card gw-stack--sm">
          <h2 class="gw-heading-s"><a class="gw-link" href="/get-started/architecture/">Architecture overview</a></h2>
          <p class="gw-body--sm">How the two-tier token architecture is wired, and the seam between primitives and semantic tokens.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
